A mother has been fined £500 after her son spent just three days in school out of a possible 118, it was revealed today.

Nicola Duke was one of three parents prosecuted last week for failing to ensure their child attends Furness Academy in Barrow, Cumbria, and she was fined £500 plus £120 of other costs.

But figures obtained since the conviction showed her son spent just three days in school between January and July 2013.

