The figures also revealed how a fellow pupil had a 26 per cent attendance record - spending 30 days at school out of 118. That pupil's father, Christian Ryan, 37, was fined £1,170 including costs.

And Karen Bromley pleaded guilty to failing to make her son attend Furness Academy and was given a 12-month conditional discharge and ordered to pay a £15 victim surcharge.

The figures show her son had an attendance record of 22 per cent - meaning he was at school for 26 days out of a possible 118.

Last month, Furness Academy revealed that Des Herlihy, who was appointed interim headteacher in June 2013, will remain as executive principal until July 2015.

